# TANAW ONE APP — Architecture Quick Reference

## 4-Layer Module Pattern

```
feature.schema.ts      -> Zod schemas + DTO types ONLY
feature.service.ts     -> Logic + Prisma ONLY. No req/res.
feature.controller.ts  -> HTTP only. Calls service. Calls sendSuccess. No try/catch.
feature.router.ts      -> Routes only.
```

## Request Flow

```
Request -> Router -> validate() -> [authMiddleware] -> Controller -> Service -> Prisma
                                                                        |
                                                              errorMiddleware (on throw)
```

## Rules

R1  Layer separation — nothing crosses layers.
R2  Services throw AppError. Controllers = zero try/catch.
R3  All responses: `{ success, message, data/errors }` via sendSuccess/sendError.
R4  Every POST/PATCH: `validate(Schema)` before controller.
R5  Public: validate -> ctrl. Protected: authMiddleware -> ctrl. Role: authMiddleware -> requireRole() -> ctrl.
R6  No Prisma in controllers. Controllers call services.
R7  `bcrypt.hash(password, 12)`. Always strip passwordHash.
R8  `import { env } from '../config/env'` — never process.env.
R9  `prisma.$transaction()` for multi-step writes.
R10 TANAW ID: `TAN-{PREFIX}-{YEAR}-{00001}` via `generateTanawId(role)`.

## TANAW ID

```
TAN-RES-2026-00001   RESIDENT            (open registration)
TAN-BGY-2026-00001   BARANGAY_OFFICIAL   (needs barangayCode, e.g. BGY-SALA-001)
TAN-GOV-2026-00001   GOVERNMENT_EMPLOYEE (needs employeeCode, e.g. EMP-CHO-2025-001)
```

